<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Comments: The name 
<taxonomicName authority="Curtis" authorityName="Curtis" box="[414,580,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solani">
<emphasis box="[414,482,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">solani</emphasis>
(Curtis)
</taxonomicName>
has often been used for this species. The position of this and some other Curtis names was discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson" box="[501,780,260,285]" pageId="45" pageNumber="63" refString="Wilson, M. R. &amp; Walker, K. (2007) John Curtis and his leafhoppers with nomenclatural notes on some species (Hemiptera, Auchenorrhyncha, Cicadellidae) with special reference to the status of Eupteryx solani Curtis 1846. Acta Entomologica Slovenica, 15, 161 - 170." type="journal article" year="2007">
Wilson &amp; Walker (
<number box="[711,773,260,284]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. In the absence of a clear description and any 
<typeStatus box="[1290,1338,261,285]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">type</typeStatus>
material the species was regarded as nomen dubium and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom" authorityName="Dahlbom" box="[684,880,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Typhlocyba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pteridis">
<emphasis box="[684,769,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">pteridis</emphasis>
Dahlbom
</taxonomicName>
(clarified by Ossiannilsson (
<number box="[1201,1258,296,320]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" value="1937.0">1937</number>
)) is regarded as the valid name.
</paragraph>
